JavaScript Programming Guide
Introduction to JavaScript
JavaScript is a versatile, high-level programming language that is primarily
used for web development. It enables interactive web pages and is an essential
part of web applications.
Key Features:
 Dynamic typing
 First-class functions
 Prototype-based object-orientation
 Event-driven programming
 Asynchronous programming support
Basic Syntax:
Variables:
let name = "Bob";
const age = 30;
var isStudent = true;
Functions:
function greet(name) {
    return ;
}
Arrow Functions:
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
Objects:
const person = {
    name: "Alice",
    age: 25,
    greet() {

        return ;
    }
};
